message.text:
I just wanna rant about the ID issue na every time na I tap kapag lalabas and papasok sa campus, ang lumalabas is BARRED—and ganito na siya since last Tuesday afternoon (morning okay pa naman siya). I thought okay lang since wala akong pasok Wednesday and Thursday, and Friday online class ako. Pero nung bumalik ako sa FEU Friday for activity groupings, I just found myself na kailangan pa pumunta sa Engr. Building to get a TEMPORARY ID kasi hindi nagwo-work yung ID ko.

They told me na pumunta ako Treasurer’s Office to check if na-settle na yung payment ko (take note: nag-downpayment na ako ng ₱9,000 agad after ko mag-enroll, and then nagbayad na ulit ako for the remaining balance of my tuition fee). So today, I went to school para ipa-fix yung ID ko since vacant naman ako. BUT AGAIN, I found myself na pinagpapasahan from Treasurer’s Office to Educ Building (IT for ID fixing). From Treasurer’s Office Counter 10 to Educ Building (IT) second floor to back to Counter 10 na pinasa sa Counter 8, tapos si Counter 8 pinasa kay Counter 6 and then si Counter 6 told me to go back to Educ Building (second floor) to check if may other issues pa sa ID ko. Pagpunta ko dun, pinabalik naman ako from Educ Building to Treasurer’s Office Counter 6—only to find it closed and my ID still not fixed. (maaga pa and one hour ako na ganto sa campus)

Nag-picture pa si kuya IT ng computer niya para ipakita ko daw sa Treasurer’s Office yung sinasabi nila kasi sila daw mag-aayos ng part na yun.

Ito pa yung nakasulat sa system nila, and ito rin yung sinabi nung nag-ask ako ng help sa TamAssist nung nag-email ako about sa ID issue:

“Student is blocked from entry in the campus. Pls. advise the Security to escort the student to the Treasurer’s Office to REGISTER their enrollment. IDs will only be activated once enrollment is registered. Thank you. - Pending.”

So bakit hindi na lang kayo mag-usap—Treasurer’s Office and Educ Building (IT, 2nd floor Educ Building)—para matapos na ‘to?

And for FEU, ang mahal ng tuition fee at miscellaneous fee niyo, pero you’re not providing better service. Tapos you even planned to increase tuition fee kahit may online classes na every thursday to saturday and yung facilities niyo hindi naman namin fully nagagamit. r u scammer or corrupt just like our politician?

message.text:
It’s my 21st birthday tomorrow… but YOU get the gift! ✨🌸

To celebrate, Kalimuyak Blooms is giving away a gorgeous 21-rose bouquet to one lucky winner. Because birthdays are always sweeter when shared. 💐❤️

How to join:
1️⃣ Like & Follow our page on FB and IG
2️⃣ Share this post to your story + comment your proof here
3️⃣ Tag a friend below

📌 Deadline to join: September 30, 2025 at 11:59 PM
📢 Winner will be announced: October 1, 2025 at 10:00 AM

Super easy, and you might just be the one to receive these lovely blooms. 🌹💖

Good luck! Let’s make this birthday extra special together. 🎉

message.text: Far Eastern University statement against corruption and the abuse of public office

feedback_target_with_context.comment_composer_placeholder: Comment as Jhon Khiel Cymon Empeno

notice_message.text: Commenting has been turned off for this post.

body.text:
This is a matter of reputation and accountability. 

The university's message is a bold declaration, but a declaration is only as strong as the actions that follow it. 

To truly rebuild public trust, they must do more than just condemn corruption; they must prove their commitment to transparency.

​The talk of "due process" is wise, as it prevents reckless accusations. 

But the real measure of their resolve will be in how they handle those accusations—with an open hand, and an honest heart. Only then will their words carry weight.

They are guided by their mission and values, and that they will uphold accountability and transparency.

This is an admirable stance.

However, the true test will be in the implementation. 

A mere statement, no matter how eloquent, is just a promise. 

A true leader fulfills promises.
